1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,800
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听 EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,800 --> 00:00:04,800
My name is Marco.
我是 Marco。

3
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:10,400
My name is Catherine and today we're tackling a very difficult issue for many English learners.
我是 Catherine，今天我们讨论一个很多英语学习者觉得棘手的问题。

4
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:14,480
We're talking about taking things from other people and giving them back.
我们要聊的是从别人那里拿东西再还回去。

5
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:15,480
That's right.
没错。

6
00:00:15,480 --> 00:00:19,780
So today we are going to talk about money and we're going to lend money and borrow money
所以今天我们要谈钱，我们会讨论借钱和贷款。

7
00:00:19,780 --> 00:00:30,380
and we're going to talk more about this after we listen to the dialogue.
听完对话后，我们再详细聊聊这个话题。

8
00:00:30,380 --> 00:00:31,380
Can I borrow five bucks?
能借我五块钱吗？

9
00:00:31,380 --> 00:00:32,380
No.
不行。

10
00:00:32,380 --> 00:00:33,380
Come on.
别这样嘛。

11
00:00:33,380 --> 00:00:35,260
I'll pay you back on Tuesday.
我周二还你。

12
00:00:35,260 --> 00:00:37,780
Last time I lent you money you never paid me back.
上次我借钱给你，你根本没还。

13
00:00:37,780 --> 00:00:43,020
I promise if you lend me five dollars today I will repay you in full next week.
我保证，如果你今天借我五美元，我下周全额还你。

14
00:00:43,020 --> 00:00:44,020
Okay.
好吧。

15
00:00:44,020 --> 00:00:45,860
But I'm taking your skateboard as collateral.
但我要拿你的滑板当抵押品。

16
00:00:45,860 --> 00:00:46,860
Fine.
行。

17
00:00:46,860 --> 00:00:48,500
I can't believe you don't trust me.
真不敢相信你不信任我。

18
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:49,900
It's nothing personal.
这不是针对你。

19
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:50,900
Just business.
只是公事公办。

20
00:00:50,900 --> 00:00:54,500
All right.
好吧。

21
00:00:54,500 --> 00:01:00,060
So now let's take a look at that language on Language Takeaway.
现在让我们看看“语言要点”部分的内容。

22
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:02,640
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

23
00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:05,300
So first up we have the key verbs for today.
首先，我们今天的关键动词。

24
00:01:05,300 --> 00:01:08,620
The verb to borrow and to lend.
动词“借入”和“借出”。

25
00:01:08,620 --> 00:01:13,140
Now this is a really important difference to make because many people make this mistake
这是一个非常重要的区别，因为很多人会犯错误。

26
00:01:13,140 --> 00:01:15,100
where they use the wrong verb.
用错动词。

27
00:01:15,100 --> 00:01:19,860
Now if I ask you Marco, can I borrow your bicycle?
如果我问你 Marco，我能借你的自行车吗？

28
00:01:19,860 --> 00:01:24,380
That means can I take your bicycle from you and then later I'll give it back.
意思是，我能从你那里拿走自行车，然后稍后还给你。

29
00:01:24,380 --> 00:01:25,580
But I want to use it.
但我想用它。

30
00:01:25,580 --> 00:01:26,580
Right.
对。

31
00:01:26,580 --> 00:01:27,580
So the verb is kind of reflexive.
所以这个动词有点反身性。

32
00:01:27,580 --> 00:01:28,580
It's going on to you.
它指向你。

33
00:01:28,580 --> 00:01:30,380
You want to borrow.
你想借。

34
00:01:30,380 --> 00:01:31,380
I want to borrow.
我想借。

35
00:01:31,380 --> 00:01:34,700
I want to take it from you for a short time and then I want to give it back.
我想从你那里暂时拿走，然后还回去。

36
00:01:34,700 --> 00:01:36,540
So to borrow.
所以是“借入”。

37
00:01:36,540 --> 00:01:42,820
Now the other verb is to lend and that on the other hand goes from me to you.
另一个动词是“借出”，它从我这到你那。

38
00:01:42,820 --> 00:01:45,980
So you borrow my bicycle.
所以你借我的自行车。

39
00:01:45,980 --> 00:01:48,020
I lend you my bicycle.
我借给你我的自行车。

40
00:01:48,020 --> 00:01:49,300
I give it to you.
我把它给你。

41
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:50,300
That's right.
没错。

42
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:56,860
So another way of asking can I borrow is can you lend me your bike?
所以另一种问“我能借吗”的方式是“你能借给我你的自行车吗？”

43
00:01:56,860 --> 00:01:58,420
That means can you act?
意思是，你能行动吗？

44
00:01:58,420 --> 00:02:00,380
Can you do this thing for me?
你能为我做这件事吗？

45
00:02:00,380 --> 00:02:03,840
So there's two different ways of saying it and it's very important to remember who is
所以有两种不同的说法，记住谁在做什么非常重要。

46
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:04,840
doing what.
做什么。

47
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:05,840
Exactly.
完全正确。

48
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:08,940
So remember the person taking is borrowing.
所以记住，拿东西的人是“借入”。

49
00:02:08,940 --> 00:02:11,380
The person giving is lending.
给东西的人是“借出”。

50
00:02:11,380 --> 00:02:19,220
So it's not correct to say can you borrow me your bicycle?
所以不能说“你能借给我你的自行车吗？”

51
00:02:19,220 --> 00:02:20,220
That's not right.
那不对。

52
00:02:20,220 --> 00:02:21,220
No.
不。

53
00:02:21,220 --> 00:02:22,220
Can you lend me?
你能借给我吗？

54
00:02:22,220 --> 00:02:24,000
Like can you lend me a hand?
比如“你能帮我一把吗？”

55
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,000
Can you help me?
你能帮我吗？

56
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Right.
对。

57
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,000
So remember this.
所以记住这个。

58
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:28,000
To borrow is something I do.
“借入”是我做的事。

59
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:31,380
I want to borrow from you.
我想从你那里借。

60
00:02:31,380 --> 00:02:33,060
It's the person, the subject in a sentence.
它是句子中的主语。

61
00:02:33,060 --> 00:02:35,860
But in the case of lending, someone else is doing it.
但在“借出”的情况下，是别人在做。

62
00:02:35,860 --> 00:02:39,480
So can you lend to me or can you lend it to him?
所以“你能借给我吗”或“你能借给他吗？”

63
00:02:39,480 --> 00:02:41,580
You have to say who it's being lent to.
你必须说明借给谁。

64
00:02:41,580 --> 00:02:42,580
Exactly.
完全正确。

65
00:02:42,580 --> 00:02:45,340
And as you said who it's being lent to.
正如你所说，要说明借给谁。

66
00:02:45,340 --> 00:02:49,100
So the past tense of lend is lent.
所以“借出”的过去式是“lent”。

67
00:02:49,100 --> 00:02:50,100
Yeah.
是的。

68
00:02:50,100 --> 00:02:54,420
So Marco lent me his bike last week and I broke it.
所以 Marco 上周借给我他的自行车，我把它弄坏了。

69
00:02:54,420 --> 00:02:56,780
So now I have to pay him a lot of money.
所以现在我必须赔他很多钱。

70
00:02:56,780 --> 00:03:00,580
You have to pay me five bucks and that's our next word, bucks.
你得赔我五块钱，这就是我们的下一个词，“bucks”。

71
00:03:00,580 --> 00:03:01,580
Bucks.
“Bucks”。

72
00:03:01,580 --> 00:03:03,680
Now this is a slang term.
这是一个俚语。

73
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:09,060
So this is something we say very casually in America when we want to talk about dollars.
在美国，当我们想谈论美元时，这是一个很随意的说法。

74
00:03:09,060 --> 00:03:11,420
So one buck is one dollar.
所以一“buck”就是一美元。

75
00:03:11,420 --> 00:03:13,620
A hundred bucks is a hundred dollars.
一百“bucks”就是一百美元。

76
00:03:13,620 --> 00:03:14,620
All right.
好的。

77
00:03:14,620 --> 00:03:16,060
Now as you said it's very American.
正如你所说，这很美国化。

78
00:03:16,060 --> 00:03:19,540
You wouldn't really use it like, I don't know if you're in Britain, you wouldn't say a hundred
你不会真的用它，比如，我不知道如果你在英国，你不会说一百“bucks”。

79
00:03:19,540 --> 00:03:20,540
bucks.
“bucks”。

80
00:03:20,540 --> 00:03:21,540
No, you would say quid.
不，你会说“quid”。

81
00:03:21,540 --> 00:03:22,540
Quid.
英镑。

82
00:03:22,540 --> 00:03:23,540
Yeah, exactly.
对，没错。

83
00:03:23,540 --> 00:03:25,180
So they don't have dollars so they don't say bucks.
所以他们不用美元，也就不说“bucks”。

84
00:03:25,180 --> 00:03:26,180
Not in England.
在英国不是这样。

85
00:03:26,180 --> 00:03:27,180
All right.
好的。

86
00:03:27,180 --> 00:03:28,180
Very good.
很好。

87
00:03:28,180 --> 00:03:36,460
So we wanted to borrow five dollars and that person promised to pay you back on Tuesday.
所以我们想借五美元，那个人答应周二还你。

88
00:03:36,460 --> 00:03:38,300
I'll pay you back on Tuesday.
我周二还你钱。

89
00:03:38,300 --> 00:03:39,300
All right.
好的。

90
00:03:39,300 --> 00:03:41,100
So this is a lot like that verb to lend.
这跟动词“lend”很像。

91
00:03:41,100 --> 00:03:46,500
To lend him, to pay you, you have to say who you're going to pay, right?
借给他、还给你，你得说清楚要还给谁，对吧？

92
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:48,580
So Marco, I'm sorry about your bicycle.
所以，Marco，关于你的自行车我很抱歉。

93
00:03:48,580 --> 00:03:50,300
I will pay you back tomorrow.
我明天还你钱。

94
00:03:50,300 --> 00:03:51,300
Okay.
好的。

95
00:03:51,300 --> 00:03:54,860
That means I will give you money for it tomorrow.
意思是明天我会给你钱补偿。

96
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:59,100
So if you borrow money, you have to pay it back.
所以如果你借钱，就得还钱。

97
00:03:59,100 --> 00:04:00,100
All right.
好的。

98
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:02,060
So I want to borrow five dollars.
所以我想借五美元。

99
00:04:02,060 --> 00:04:05,420
I promise I will pay you back Thursday.
我保证周四还你。

100
00:04:05,420 --> 00:04:06,420
Very good.
很好。

101
00:04:06,420 --> 00:04:07,420
Okay.
好的。

102
00:04:07,420 --> 00:04:12,940
So now lastly, we will lend money, but of course we need a guarantee.
最后，我们会借钱，但当然需要担保。

103
00:04:12,940 --> 00:04:15,780
We need something to make sure that you will pay me back.
我们需要一些东西来确保你会还我钱。

104
00:04:15,780 --> 00:04:17,940
So that's called collateral.
这就叫抵押品。

105
00:04:17,940 --> 00:04:18,940
All right.
好的。

106
00:04:18,940 --> 00:04:25,180
Now collateral is important because sometimes you can't trust someone, like you say, Marco.
抵押品很重要，因为有时候你不能信任别人，就像你说的，Marco。

107
00:04:25,180 --> 00:04:29,700
And so for example, if I want to rent a bicycle, so I want to use it for the day, maybe there's
比如，如果我想租一辆自行车，用一天，可能有个

108
00:04:29,700 --> 00:04:32,900
a store that they rent bicycles to people.
商店出租自行车给人们。

109
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:39,740
I would give my passport or my driver's license as collateral because I will definitely return
我会把护照或驾照作为抵押品，因为我肯定会回来

110
00:04:39,740 --> 00:04:42,500
to take my driver's license or passport back.
取回我的驾照或护照。

111
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:51,140
So that's basically a sign of a promise, money or identification or some object.
所以这基本上是一种承诺的象征，可以是钱、身份证明或某个物品。

112
00:04:51,140 --> 00:04:52,140
That's right.
没错。

113
00:04:52,140 --> 00:04:55,380
So usually, for example, if you're going to get a very big loan at the bank, they will
所以通常，比如，如果你要从银行贷一大笔款，他们会

114
00:04:55,380 --> 00:04:57,900
ask you for something as collateral.
要求你提供一些东西作为抵押品。

115
00:04:57,900 --> 00:05:01,220
So maybe you will have to give them your house as collateral.
所以你可能得把房子作为抵押品。

116
00:05:01,220 --> 00:05:04,900
So you're saying if I can't pay you back, then you can take my house.
所以你是说，如果我还不了钱，你就可以拿走我的房子。

117
00:05:04,900 --> 00:05:05,900
That's right.
没错。

118
00:05:05,900 --> 00:05:09,480
So collateral is the last word in language takeaway, but we do have some great phrases
所以“抵押品”是语言总结的最后一个词，但我们还有一些很棒的短语

119
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:13,100
for you coming up in Fluency Builder.
在流利度训练中要介绍给你。

120
00:05:13,100 --> 00:05:20,620
Can I borrow five bucks?
能借我五块钱吗？

121
00:05:20,620 --> 00:05:21,620
No.
不行。

122
00:05:21,620 --> 00:05:22,620
Come on.
别这样。

123
00:05:22,620 --> 00:05:24,180
I'll pay you back on Tuesday.
我周二还你。

124
00:05:24,180 --> 00:05:26,660
Last time I lent you money, you never paid me back.
上次我借钱给你，你一直没还。

125
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:31,820
I promise if you lend me five dollars today, I will repay you in full next week.
我保证如果你今天借我五美元，我下周全额还你。

126
00:05:31,820 --> 00:05:34,780
OK, but I'm taking your skateboard as collateral.
好吧，但我拿你的滑板当抵押品。

127
00:05:34,780 --> 00:05:35,780
Fine.
行。

128
00:05:35,780 --> 00:05:37,380
I can't believe you don't trust me.
真不敢相信你不信任我。

129
00:05:37,380 --> 00:05:39,900
It's nothing personal, just business.
这不是针对个人，只是公事公办。

130
00:05:39,900 --> 00:05:43,500
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

131
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:49,180
So let's take a look at these phrases on Fluency Builder.
让我们看看流利度训练中的这些短语。

132
00:05:49,180 --> 00:05:50,180
Fluency Builder.
流利度训练。

133
00:05:50,180 --> 00:05:55,740
So, Marco, these are two friends talking and the way they talk to each other is very casual,
所以，Marco，这是两个朋友在聊天，他们说话的方式很随意，

134
00:05:55,740 --> 00:05:59,540
so we hear at the beginning, can I borrow five bucks?
所以我们一开始听到“能借我五块钱吗？”

135
00:05:59,540 --> 00:06:00,540
No.
不行。

136
00:06:00,540 --> 00:06:01,540
Come on.
别这样。

137
00:06:01,540 --> 00:06:02,540
Right.
对。

138
00:06:02,540 --> 00:06:03,540
So what is this?
这是什么意思？

139
00:06:03,540 --> 00:06:04,540
Come on.
别这样。

140
00:06:04,540 --> 00:06:06,500
It's a persuasive phrase.
这是一个说服性的短语。

141
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:11,020
It's one of those phrases where you're trying to convince or persuade people and you can
这是那种你试图说服或劝服别人时用的短语，在很多情况下

142
00:06:11,020 --> 00:06:14,180
use it as an interjection in many situations.
都可以用作感叹词。

143
00:06:14,180 --> 00:06:17,300
So for example, here, come on, lend it to me.
比如，这里，“别这样，借给我吧。”

144
00:06:17,300 --> 00:06:18,300
Lend me some money.
借我点钱。

145
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:19,300
I'll pay you back.
我会还你的。

146
00:06:19,300 --> 00:06:20,300
You're trying to convince that person.
你在试图说服那个人。

147
00:06:20,300 --> 00:06:21,300
Please.
求你了。

148
00:06:21,300 --> 00:06:22,300
Yeah, exactly.
对，没错。

149
00:06:22,300 --> 00:06:24,420
But what about this situation?
但这种情况呢？

150
00:06:24,420 --> 00:06:25,540
I'm running late.
我要迟到了。

151
00:06:25,540 --> 00:06:32,860
I have to go and my friend, she's still sitting at her desk, maybe at work and it's taking
我得走了，我的朋友还坐在办公桌前，可能在工作，而且她

152
00:06:32,860 --> 00:06:33,860
forever.
拖了很久。

153
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:34,860
I say, come on, let's go.
我说，“快点，我们走吧。”

154
00:06:34,860 --> 00:06:35,860
Right.
对。

155
00:06:35,860 --> 00:06:36,860
It's like, hurry up, move it.
就像“快点，动起来。”

156
00:06:36,860 --> 00:06:37,860
All right.
好的。

157
00:06:37,860 --> 00:06:40,140
So it's a way of getting someone to do something.
所以这是一种让别人做某事的方式。

158
00:06:40,140 --> 00:06:42,220
You want them to follow you.
你想让他们跟着你。

159
00:06:42,220 --> 00:06:43,220
Exactly.
没错。

160
00:06:43,220 --> 00:06:48,420
And now talking about money again, the person promised to repay the money.
现在又说到钱，那个人承诺会还钱。

161
00:06:48,420 --> 00:06:49,980
He said, I'll pay you back on Tuesday.
他说，我星期二还你钱。

162
00:06:49,980 --> 00:06:55,740
But then he also said, I will repay you in full next week.
但接着他又说，我下周全额还你。

163
00:06:55,740 --> 00:06:56,740
In full.
全额。

164
00:06:56,740 --> 00:06:57,740
Now, remember, this is important.
现在，记住，这点很重要。

165
00:06:57,740 --> 00:06:59,540
I will repay you in full.
我会全额还你。

166
00:06:59,540 --> 00:07:03,580
That means I won't repay you a little bit and then a little bit later.
这意味着我不会先还一点，再还一点。

167
00:07:03,580 --> 00:07:06,660
I will repay you everything next week.
我下周会一次性还清所有钱。

168
00:07:06,660 --> 00:07:07,660
Right, exactly.
对，没错。

169
00:07:07,660 --> 00:07:13,380
So if you have to pay or repay someone in full, you have to give them the entire amount,
所以，如果你必须全额支付或偿还某人，你得给他们全部金额，

170
00:07:13,380 --> 00:07:14,900
not just a part of it.
而不是只还一部分。

171
00:07:14,900 --> 00:07:15,900
That's right.
没错。

172
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:16,900
In full.
全额。

173
00:07:16,900 --> 00:07:17,900
Full means everything.
全额就是全部。

174
00:07:17,900 --> 00:07:21,180
The final phrase is the very last line of today's dialogue.
最后一个短语是今天对话的最后一句。

175
00:07:21,180 --> 00:07:22,580
It's nothing personal.
这不是针对个人。

176
00:07:22,580 --> 00:07:23,660
It's just business.
这只是生意。

177
